  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nAs a block proposer I would like to have choice to not propose block immediately, but after X seconds in the given slot.\r\nWith MEV around, proposing blocks as late as possible will allow the block proposer to find/get more MEV opportunities.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nBecause it is risky to propose blocks late, my idea was to let the user choose how late it has to be, so:\r\n\r\n`--propose-block-late 5000 11000` where `5000` is for a single block proposal in ms and `11000` for blocks where i have two in a row (assuming no eth2 spec change and only the next block proposer needs to know about the current block, which is me).\r\n\r\nThe upper cap should be 11.x seconds\r\n",
