    "body": "I think clients should strive to do what's best for the network, I would advocate for the opposite and look for in-protocol ways to penalize late blocks. This feature would literally go against the [honest validator spec](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/validator.md#block-proposal)\r\n\r\n> A validator is expected to propose a [SignedBeaconBlock](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/beacon-chain.md#signedbeaconblock) at the beginning of any slot during which `is_proposer(state, validator_index)` returns `True`.",
